snippet.textDisplay:
Matt: starts figuring out scotts story up to help wanted

Scott: throw the entire story out. We need to keep matt confused.

Matt: y u do!?!

Scott: because i can as the game developer

Matt: begins to slam head on desk out of frustration.

Scott: yes mat, give into your anger. Embrace the dark side.

Matt: goes into super theorist mode

scott has left chat

(Edit): a theory that i have is that if you think about it, scot was writing a story and slowly starting to piece in details with fnaf 1-4, (and we all know how scott love to leave everyone trying to figure it out), he leaves one particular string left so he has a direction to go on with a different part of the story (sister location). From here he takes his time with pizzeria simulator (because im going to grasp as straws here and say because he has soooo many notes for things he wants to include into the story and how he wants to stitch it all together in the way he wants to tell it, he has to figure out how he can stitch this new game to be relevant). Once released, he steps away to work on the books because i think he is wanting to have a breather so that he can keep his formula of drooping little tid bits of lore in order (because im sure there are some really meaty tid bits of lore that he doesnt want to release but somehow felt like he was coming close to releasing them). And than come to the present with help wanted. I believe that he created help wanted to give himself the ability to tell other stories while simultaneously buying himself time to complete all the gaps in his story so far from the beginning. Thus being able to give himself the groundwork to keep making games and books for many more years to come.


And of course if that theory falls through, than im just going to go with "scott is trying to become like George Lucas by having a bunch of stories that all take place in the same universe, but have no connection to each other, other than the fact all these stories take place in the same universe".

snippet.textDisplay: So I have an idea of how glichtrap got in the game. So clearly ennard was going through the trash. In FNAF VR Help Wanted tape girl said that she used some old circutboards for her tapes. Maybe those circutboards were once a part on scrap baby or ennard. As you can see in pizzeria simulator scrap baby has been getting random stuff for herself. Ex: roller skates. It wouldn’t be to farfetched if , since fazbear intertainment probably wasn’t in the best financial situation, the tape girl just found them. They could’ve even been lost when scrap baby left ennard. But some remnant stayed with the circutboards and so did the bad memories of William Afton. So when they used the circutboards the memories of William Afton from the dead children/ animatronics also went into the game. Probably not right, but a cool theory none the less.

snippet.textDisplay: Hey MatPat, you said that Oswald sees the Golden Bonnie where his father should be, but everyone else sees his father?  Doesn't that harken back to what you said about the Help Wanted game, where it's suggested that the game tester was taken over by the digital copy of Golden Bonnie?  Also, it sort of ties into the concept of,the AR game.  You're basically playing a game with virtual characters you're able to see (via a cellphone), but no one else will.
